# <%= current_page.data.title %>

The public sector must adhere to a set of regulations designed to ensure the security, accessibility, and effectiveness of digital services. These regulations apply to Digital and Technology in the public sector, guiding the development, implementation, and management of digital initiatives to meet legal, ethical, and operational standards.

## [Accessibility Regulations 2018](https://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2018/952/contents)
Guidance: [Meet the requirements of equality and accessibility regulations](https://www.gov.uk/guidance/meet-the-requirements-of-equality-and-accessibility-regulations)

## [Data Protection Act 2018](https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2018/12/part/2/chapter/2/enacted)
Guidance: [Meet the requirements of data privacy regulations](https://www.gov.uk/guidance/meet-the-requirements-of-data-privacy-regulations)

## [Equality Act 2010](https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2010/15/contents)
Guidance: [Meet the requirements of equality and accessibility regulations](https://www.gov.uk/guidance/meet-the-requirements-of-equality-and-accessibility-regulations)

By adhering to these regulations, public sector organizations can deliver digital services that are secure, accessible, and aligned with legal and ethical standards, ultimately benefiting the public and maintaining trust in government services.
